1
00:00:29,583 --> 00:00:31,416
[KYON] During final exams,
Haruhi, who suffered a bout

2
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:33,541
of melancholy during
the Star Festival,

3
00:00:33,625 --> 00:00:35,166
had recovered from the
aforementioned melancholy

4
00:00:35,250 --> 00:00:38,291
enough to go back to doing
whatever she wanted to do.

5
00:00:38,375 --> 00:00:41,916
However, as an adverse reaction
to her emotional improvement,

6
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:43,958
the blue-colored baton
of depression had been

7
00:00:44,041 --> 00:00:45,208
handed off to me.

8
00:00:45,291 --> 00:00:46,375
[KYON sighs]

9
00:00:46,458 --> 00:00:47,791
[KYON] Haruhi always
seemed to have time

10
00:00:47,875 --> 00:00:50,625
left over during an exam,
and today was no exception

11
00:00:50,708 --> 00:00:53,708
About 30 minutes before pencils
down, she was sound asleep

12
00:00:53,791 --> 00:00:55,500
in the desk behind me.

13
00:00:55,583 --> 00:00:59,041
Annoying. Oh, it's annoying.
It's so annoying.

14
00:02:29,875 --> 00:02:30,833
[KYON]
According to Haruhi,

15
00:02:30,916 --> 00:02:32,083
there is no such
thing as a break

16
00:02:32,166 --> 00:02:33,666
for the SOS Brigade.

17
00:02:33,750 --> 00:02:36,791
Even during exam time, when all
the other clubs went on hiatus,

18
00:02:36,875 --> 00:02:39,750
this mysterious brigade,
which wasn't really even a club,

19
00:02:39,833 --> 00:02:41,958
was open every day
without a holiday.

20
00:02:42,041 --> 00:02:44,333
Kinda like a convenient store...

21
00:02:44,416 --> 00:02:46,875
[HARUHI]
Hey, come take a look at this.

22
00:02:52,208 --> 00:02:53,000
[KYON]
What is it?

23
00:02:53,083 --> 00:02:54,416
You can't tell what it is?

24
00:02:54,500 --> 00:02:56,875
I've no idea.
I don't get it at all.

25
00:02:56,958 --> 00:02:59,500
It's the logo for
the SOS Brigade.

26
00:02:59,583 --> 00:03:02,250
A logo? That's funny, 'cause
to me, it looks more like

27
00:03:02,333 --> 00:03:04,208
a drunken tapeworm
wrapped around a tube.

28
00:03:04,291 --> 00:03:06,250
Well, take a closer look at it!

29
00:03:06,333 --> 00:03:11,250
See, it says "SOS Brigade"
right there in the middle!

30
00:03:11,333 --> 00:03:13,458
[KYON] Now that she pointed it
out, I can't really say for sure

31
00:03:13,541 --> 00:03:15,666
whether I can or can't
see it, but I wouldn't

32
00:03:15,750 --> 00:03:18,208
disagree with anybody if
they said it was or wasn't.

33
00:03:18,291 --> 00:03:20,875
And how many negatives did
I just use in that sentence?

34
00:03:20,958 --> 00:03:23,083
If somebody's got time,
total it up for me.

35
00:03:23,166 --> 00:03:25,791
You're the one that's
got the most free time.

36
00:03:25,875 --> 00:03:27,333
Anyway, I was thinking
of putting this thing

37
00:03:27,416 --> 00:03:29,958
on the homepage of the
SOS Brigade website.

38
00:03:30,041 --> 00:03:31,208
[KYON]
You mean, this pathetic website

39
00:03:31,291 --> 00:03:32,833
that only has a homepage?

40
00:03:32,916 --> 00:03:36,250
This website that you made isn't
getting us any visitors at all.

41
00:03:36,333 --> 00:03:37,708
It's so frustrating.

42
00:03:37,791 --> 00:03:39,958
There's nothing on here
that spices it up.

43
00:03:40,041 --> 00:03:41,833
It's all because
you got in my way.

44
00:03:41,916 --> 00:03:43,833
We'd've had a ton of hits
if you'd let me post

45
00:03:43,916 --> 00:03:46,916
these erotic pics of Mikuru.
So I got to thinkin',

46
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:49,625
I should paste a cool logo or
symbol for the SOS Brigade

47
00:03:49,708 --> 00:03:51,041
on the homepage.

48
00:03:51,125 --> 00:03:53,083
[KYON] Just get this stupid
excuse for a website

49
00:03:53,166 --> 00:03:54,583
off the net already.

50
00:03:54,666 --> 00:03:57,041
The access counter hasn't
even reached three digits yet,

51
00:03:57,125 --> 00:04:01,041
and 90% of those hits have been
you checking the site for hits.

52
00:04:01,125 --> 00:04:03,000
Write a blog on
there or something.

53
00:04:03,083 --> 00:04:04,500
Isn't it your job
to keep a record

54
00:04:04,583 --> 00:04:05,833
of the brigade's activities?

55
00:04:05,916 --> 00:04:07,375
Ugh, too much of a hassle.

56
00:04:07,458 --> 00:04:09,583
[KYON]
Well, it's a hassle for me, too.

57
00:04:10,666 --> 00:04:13,333
Okay, Kyon, your job for
today is to make this logo

58
00:04:13,416 --> 00:04:15,416
show up on the homepage
of the website.

59
00:04:15,500 --> 00:04:17,083
[KYON]
Why don't you do it yourself?

60
00:04:17,166 --> 00:04:19,916
I'm the brigade leader! It's
the job of the brigade leader

61
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:22,541
to give the orders!
Besides, if I did everything,

62
00:04:22,625 --> 00:04:25,250
there'd be nothing left for you
guys to do, isn't that right?

63
00:04:25,333 --> 00:04:27,375
I'm always spelling this stuff
out for you, why don't you

64
00:04:27,458 --> 00:04:29,666
use your head? How do you
expect to improve yourself

65
00:04:29,750 --> 00:04:31,166
if you only do what you're told?

66
00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:32,875
There you go, talking
in circles again.

67
00:04:32,958 --> 00:04:35,625
Are you telling me to do it
or not to do it? Which is it?

68
00:04:35,708 --> 00:04:37,375
[HARUHI]
Enough! Get on it!

69
00:04:37,458 --> 00:04:39,583
[sighs]

70
00:04:39,666 --> 00:04:42,833
[KYON] Reluctantly, I shrunk the
master painter Haruhi's tapeworm

71
00:04:42,916 --> 00:04:46,791
into an appropriate size. Then,
I pasted it, still reluctantly,

72
00:04:46,875 --> 00:04:49,708
into the file, and uploaded it.

73
00:04:49,791 --> 00:04:52,250
Starting tomorrow and lasting
until summer vacation,

74
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:54,375
we get to have our exam break.

75
00:04:54,458 --> 00:04:58,166
It's also the time when my
teacher's mark my answers wrong.

76
00:04:58,250 --> 00:04:59,875
Damn, that's annoying.

77
00:04:59,958 --> 00:05:03,458
Guess I'll go and ogle
Miss Asahina for some comfort.

78
00:05:03,541 --> 00:05:05,916
I knocked on the door, fully
expecting Miss Asahina's voice

79
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,833
to call out a wispy
"Yes" in reply.

80
00:05:07,916 --> 00:05:10,000
--[knocks]
--[HARUHI] Come in.

81
00:05:11,666 --> 00:05:13,291
[KYON]
You're the only one here?

82
00:05:13,375 --> 00:05:15,125
Yuki's here, too.

83
00:05:16,166 --> 00:05:18,000
[KYON] She's more like
an accessory to the room,

84
00:05:18,083 --> 00:05:20,041
so you can't really
count her as a member.

85
00:05:20,125 --> 00:05:22,833
I mean, officially, she's a
member of the Literary Club,

86
00:05:22,916 --> 00:05:25,000
so I guess I should
correct myself.

87
00:05:25,083 --> 00:05:27,250
You and Nagato are
the only ones here?

88
00:05:27,333 --> 00:05:29,708
[HARUHI] You wanna file
a complaint about it?

89
00:05:29,791 --> 00:05:31,875
[KYON] If I wrote down every
complaint I had about you,

90
00:05:31,958 --> 00:05:36,083
it would fill up an entire sheet
of A4-size paper, both sides.

91
00:05:36,166 --> 00:05:37,583
When you knocked on
the door just now,

92
00:05:37,666 --> 00:05:40,166
I thought for sure we were
going to have a visitor today.

93
00:05:40,250 --> 00:05:42,750
[KYON] Just being careful. I
don't wanna accidentally walk in

94
00:05:42,833 --> 00:05:45,083
while Miss Asahina's changing.

95
00:05:45,166 --> 00:05:48,083
[KYON] That lovely, innocent
young girl just can't seem

96
00:05:48,166 --> 00:05:50,041
to figure out how
to lock a door.

97
00:05:50,125 --> 00:05:52,125
So now, what's all
this about a visitor?

98
00:05:52,208 --> 00:05:53,958
Don't tell me you
don't remember?

99
00:05:54,041 --> 00:05:55,166
[KYON] I hope she isn't
gonna say anything

100
00:05:55,250 --> 00:05:57,583
about the Star Festival
three years ago.

101
00:05:57,666 --> 00:05:59,416
Oh, come on, it's
something you did,

102
00:05:59,500 --> 00:06:01,416
and without getting
my permission first.

103
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:03,166
I have no idea what
you're talking about.

104
00:06:03,250 --> 00:06:05,583
Those posters you put up
all over the school.

105
00:06:05,666 --> 00:06:08,458
Right, those things.

106
00:06:08,541 --> 00:06:10,041
[KYON]
Those posters were my attempt

107
00:06:10,125 --> 00:06:12,333
at getting the student council
to keep the SOS Brigade alive

108
00:06:12,416 --> 00:06:15,541
as a sort of jack-of-all-
-trades counseling thing.

109
00:06:15,625 --> 00:06:17,291
I even drew them all
and stuck them up

110
00:06:17,375 --> 00:06:19,833
on every bulletin board
in the school.

111
00:06:19,916 --> 00:06:21,500
[HARUHI]
Anyway, take a look at this.

112
00:06:21,583 --> 00:06:23,416
Something weird's
happening here.

113
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:27,041
Maybe it's just the
computer acting up.

114
00:06:27,125 --> 00:06:29,875
[KYON] The SOS Brigade's logo
was warped, as if somebody used

115
00:06:29,958 --> 00:06:31,458
a gathering filter on it.

116
00:06:31,541 --> 00:06:34,083
On top of that, the counter
and title were gone.

117
00:06:34,166 --> 00:06:37,208
It was subtle, but it was
different from the page I made.

118
00:06:39,416 --> 00:06:41,666
It looks like the file on
the server has been corrupted.

119
00:06:41,750 --> 00:06:43,541
So do you know how long
it's been like this?

120
00:06:43,625 --> 00:06:46,000
No, it was like that
when I checked it today.

121
00:06:46,083 --> 00:06:48,125
Who do I complain to about this?

122
00:06:48,208 --> 00:06:50,500
[KYON] It isn't worth
filing a complaint.

123
00:06:53,291 --> 00:06:54,541
[KYON]
Hm?

124
00:06:54,625 --> 00:06:55,833
[KYON growls]

125
00:06:57,208 --> 00:07:00,166
It's weird. Wait, I know,
it's hackers or crackers

126
00:07:00,250 --> 00:07:01,791
or whatever they're called.

127
00:07:01,875 --> 00:07:04,416
No way. It's probably
just an error.

128
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:06,958
It's so irritating. I can't
believe someone would make

129
00:07:07,041 --> 00:07:09,750
a cyber terrorist attack
on the SOS Brigade!

130
00:07:09,833 --> 00:07:12,208
Oh, when I find out who's
doing this, I'll make 'em do

131
00:07:12,291 --> 00:07:14,958
30 days of community
service, no trial!

132
00:07:15,041 --> 00:07:16,333
[knocking]

133
00:07:16,416 --> 00:07:17,958
Come in.

134
00:07:18,041 --> 00:07:21,958
Well, this is unusual. Miss
Asahina hasn't shown up yet?

135
00:07:22,041 --> 00:07:24,750
[HARUHI] The juniors have more
exams to take, don't they?

136
00:07:24,833 --> 00:07:27,333
[KYON] Hey, everyone, just
hurry up and go home already.

137
00:07:27,416 --> 00:07:29,958
I mean, of all places,
why do you wanna meet here?

138
00:07:30,041 --> 00:07:32,166
Oh, and Haruhi, is there
any special reason

139
00:07:32,250 --> 00:07:35,500
you're not saying anything
about Koizumi knocking?

140
00:07:39,375 --> 00:07:42,250
[KYON] I'm looking forward
to Miss Asahina's tea.

141
00:07:42,333 --> 00:07:44,416
[KYON grunting]

142
00:07:44,500 --> 00:07:46,541
[HARUHI]
That's not it! No, to the right!

143
00:07:46,625 --> 00:07:48,750
[KYON] For a while, I found
myself stuck there catering

144
00:07:48,833 --> 00:07:50,791
to Haruhi's impossible orders.

145
00:07:50,875 --> 00:07:53,250
--[knocking]
--That's not it!

146
00:07:53,333 --> 00:07:54,250
--[HARUHI] Come in.
--[KYON] At last,

147
00:07:54,333 --> 00:07:56,666
the sound of my salvation.

148
00:07:56,750 --> 00:07:59,083
[MIKURU]
Uh, I'm so sorry I'm late.

149
00:07:59,166 --> 00:08:01,416
I had exams until fourth period.

150
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:04,958
[KYON] With a humble apology,
she appeared, no, descended.

151
00:08:05,041 --> 00:08:08,000
The angel of the
club, Miss Asahina.

152
00:08:08,083 --> 00:08:11,583
Well, I, um... Let's see...

153
00:08:13,083 --> 00:08:16,375
I, um, I sort of brought
a visitor with me.

154
00:08:21,750 --> 00:08:23,541
[KYON] Unbelievable!
I never thought anyone

155
00:08:23,625 --> 00:08:24,916
would come to us for counseling!

156
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:27,125
But somehow has,
and there she is!

157
00:08:27,208 --> 00:08:30,041
Her name was Emiri Kimidori,
a junior who seemed

158
00:08:30,125 --> 00:08:31,958
very quiet and pure.

159
00:08:32,041 --> 00:08:35,041
So, lemme get this straight.
You want us, the SOS Brigade,

160
00:08:35,125 --> 00:08:38,041
to go and search for
your missing boyfriend?

161
00:08:38,125 --> 00:08:39,083
Yes...

162
00:08:39,166 --> 00:08:40,666
Hm...

163
00:08:40,750 --> 00:08:41,666
Ah.

164
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:42,833
[sighs]

165
00:08:42,916 --> 00:08:44,500
[KYON] Oh, great.
It seems that she thinks

166
00:08:44,583 --> 00:08:47,000
the purpose of the
SOS Brigade really is to be

167
00:08:47,083 --> 00:08:50,791
a mobile task force or jack-
-of-all-trades counseling-thing.

168
00:08:50,875 --> 00:08:53,958
So, what exactly
is troubling you?

169
00:08:54,041 --> 00:08:57,291
He hasn't been in school
for the longest time.

170
00:08:57,375 --> 00:08:58,750
Have you tried calling him?

171
00:08:58,833 --> 00:09:01,583
He doesn't answer his
cell or his home phone.

172
00:09:01,666 --> 00:09:04,166
I even went to his house,
but he wasn't there.

173
00:09:04,250 --> 00:09:05,625
[HARUHI]
Hm...

174
00:09:05,708 --> 00:09:07,583
What about your
boyfriend's family?

175
00:09:07,666 --> 00:09:10,000
As far as I know,
he lives alone.

176
00:09:10,083 --> 00:09:13,458
A while ago, I remember hearing
they lived and worked overseas,

177
00:09:13,541 --> 00:09:16,083
but I don't have any of
their contact information.

178
00:09:16,166 --> 00:09:18,375
Really? Well, are his
parents in Canada?

179
00:09:18,458 --> 00:09:21,208
No, I believe they live
somewhere in Honduras.

180
00:09:21,291 --> 00:09:24,416
Oh-ho, yes, Honduras! Indeed!

181
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:26,833
[KYON] What's with this "Indeed"
stuff? I doubt she even knows

182
00:09:26,916 --> 00:09:28,500
where Honduras is.

183
00:09:28,583 --> 00:09:31,375
Let's see, somewhere
below Mexico, right?

184
00:09:31,458 --> 00:09:34,583
That night when I went to see
him, the house was pitch-black.

185
00:09:34,666 --> 00:09:36,208
I'm so worried.

186
00:09:36,291 --> 00:09:39,250
Yeah, I can totally understand
how you're feeling about this.

187
00:09:39,333 --> 00:09:40,541
[KYON]
Liar. You don't understand

188
00:09:40,625 --> 00:09:41,875
the feeling of being in love.

189
00:09:41,958 --> 00:09:44,125
Anyway, I'm surprised you
came to the SOS Brigade

190
00:09:44,208 --> 00:09:46,625
with this mystery.
So why'd you come to us?

191
00:09:46,708 --> 00:09:49,250
My boyfriend used to talk
about the SOS Brigade.

192
00:09:49,333 --> 00:09:50,291
That's why I'm here.

193
00:09:50,375 --> 00:09:53,416
Oh? So who is this boyfriend?

194
00:09:54,875 --> 00:09:55,666
--Ya--
--[cat meows]

195
00:09:55,750 --> 00:09:57,083
is his name.

196
00:09:57,166 --> 00:09:59,208
Don't know him, who's he?

197
00:10:03,833 --> 00:10:04,750
[HARUHI growls]

198
00:10:04,833 --> 00:10:05,458
[KYON]
Hm?

199
00:10:05,541 --> 00:10:06,166
[MIKURU]
Hm?

200
00:10:06,250 --> 00:10:07,333
To tell you the truth,

201
00:10:07,416 --> 00:10:09,666
he's the president
of the Computer Club.

202
00:10:09,750 --> 00:10:10,833
[KYON]
Hm...

203
00:10:10,916 --> 00:10:12,500
[gasps]

204
00:10:12,583 --> 00:10:13,666
[KYON]
The guy Haruhi took pictures of

205
00:10:13,750 --> 00:10:16,500
as he sexually
harassed Miss Asahina!

206
00:10:16,583 --> 00:10:18,166
The guy Haruhi
blackmailed so she could

207
00:10:18,250 --> 00:10:21,250
take his top-of-
-the-line computer.

208
00:10:21,333 --> 00:10:23,125
The poor guy who was forced
to hook the computer up

209
00:10:23,208 --> 00:10:24,708
with tears in his eyes.

210
00:10:24,791 --> 00:10:26,458
I totally forgot about him.

211
00:10:26,541 --> 00:10:30,250
Okay, I got it. Don't worry,
we'll do something about this.

212
00:10:30,333 --> 00:10:32,583
Miss Kimidori,
today's your lucky day!

213
00:10:32,666 --> 00:10:35,000
Since you're the SOS
Brigade's first client,

214
00:10:35,083 --> 00:10:37,458
I'll solve the case of your
mystery boyfriend for free!

215
00:10:37,541 --> 00:10:39,791
[KYON] You planned on
charging money for this?

216
00:10:46,666 --> 00:10:48,125
Hey.

217
00:10:48,208 --> 00:10:49,625
Taking her case was the easy
part, but what're you gonna do

218
00:10:49,708 --> 00:10:51,666
if you can't solve it?

219
00:10:52,750 --> 00:10:54,833
We'll solve it. I'm sure
the Computer Club chief's

220
00:10:54,916 --> 00:10:56,875
suffering from the May
Melancholies, even if it's

221
00:10:56,958 --> 00:10:58,208
a couple months late.

222
00:10:58,291 --> 00:11:00,041
We'll just stroll into
his house, grab him,

223
00:11:00,125 --> 00:11:02,666
slap him around a little,
and drag him outta there.

224
00:11:02,750 --> 00:11:05,125
[KYON] I think she's serious
about that. But if he's got

225
00:11:05,208 --> 00:11:07,916
a girlfriend like Miss Kimidori,
why's that guy hiding out

226
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:10,500
in the Computer Club?

227
00:11:10,583 --> 00:11:12,791
Are you and Miss Kimidori
friends or something?

228
00:11:12,875 --> 00:11:16,791
[MIKURU] Mm-mm. I've never
spoken to her before today.

229
00:11:16,875 --> 00:11:18,041
[KYON]
If she needed help,

230
00:11:18,125 --> 00:11:20,250
why didn't she go to a
teacher or the police?

231
00:11:20,333 --> 00:11:23,125
No, maybe she did, but they
didn't take her seriously.

232
00:11:23,208 --> 00:11:25,541
That's why she came to
the SOS Brigade for help.

233
00:11:25,625 --> 00:11:27,625
Yeah, that's what's
going on here.

234
00:11:27,708 --> 00:11:29,791
Looks like Haruhi's using
this as an opportunity

235
00:11:29,875 --> 00:11:31,625
to attract bigger cases.

236
00:11:31,708 --> 00:11:34,333
Bet she can think she
can solve those, too.

237
00:11:34,416 --> 00:11:35,541
